    "Only businesses are allowed to host for-profit events on Solis. If the funds collected on Solis for an event organized by students or associations, are greater than the costs of the event, then the organizers are responsible for redistributing these funds directly in the event or indirectly. Solis is committed to protecting its community and may use personal data, including student emails and other information, to trace the identity of individuals who do not comply with these conditions. Harmful behavior during participation in events and the dissemination of false information or malicious events are subject to legal sanctions and restrictions on the part of Solis, including the suspension of events or the accounts concerned. The data collected by Solis has the sole purpose of optimizing the operation of the application and protecting this community. No data will be shared with other companies.";
